thread.title: Moscow Domodedovo Airport fire contained

author: eTN Managing Editor
title: Moscow Domodedovo Airport fire contained
text:
Moscow Domodedovo Airport fire contained   
Sep 03, 2015 eTN   
The Russian Emergency Ministry told TASS that cables had caught fire in Moscow's Domodedovo Airport baggage department, in an area covering approximately 20 square meters. 
Sixty flights have been delayed, according to the airport’s online display board. The number of delays could increase. There is information on 50 further flights coming up, both arrivals and departures. 
3,000 people have been evacuated, and the fire has been contained. 
Special equipment for removing smoke has been sent to the airport. 
"After the smoke is removed and the building is checked, the airport will continue normal service," the ministry’s spokesperson said.
